gomodel:SYNGO_4649  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Figure 3. \"High-power fluorescence micrographs of vertical sections through the inner plexiform layer of mouse retinae that were doubly labeled for GlyR α2 and synaptic markers.\"\n\n\"Figure 3D-F shows a section that was doubly labeled for GlyR α2 (Fig. 3D) and gephyrin (Fig. 3E). Superposition (Fig. 3F) shows that many of the GlyR α2 puncta coincide with gephyrin clusters (boxes in Fig. 3D-F). This was also assessed quantitatively in six sections (see Materials and Methods), and a mean coincidence rate of 46.7% ± 4.4% (mean ± SD) was found.\"\n\n\"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected based on protein's known transmembrane topology. Experimental description: \"High-power fluorescence micrographs of vertical sections through the inner plexiform layer of mouse retinae that were doubly labeled for GlyR α2 and synaptic markers.\"\n\n\"To study the expression of GlyR α2 in the retina at the protein level, a novel polyclonal antiserum against the C-terminus of the subunit was raised. However, this antiserum showed some cross-reactivity with the α1 subunit. By contrast, an additional polyclonal antiserum against the N-terminus of the GlyR α2 subunit showed no cross-reactivity with other GlyR subunits.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4649" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

